<topic xml:id="openwebui-input-field-collections"
 role="task" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>Adding preconfigured documents or external URLs from the chat input field</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tbazant@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
<!-- <xi:include href="../snippets/openwebui-intro.xml"/> -->
      <para>
        This topic explains how to add preconfigured collections of documents
        and external URLs from the chat input field.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    Besides prompting preconfigured AI models, you can <quote>talk</quote> to
    documents or collections of documents uploaded by the administrator. You can
    also specify external URLs whose content will be processed. AI then responds
    to your prompts based on the specified information sources.
  </para>
  <procedure>
    <step>
      <para>
        In the chat input field, type the <literal>#</literal> character.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <substeps>
        <step>
          <para>
            From the drop-down list that appears, select one of the
            preconfigured documents or a collection of documents whose content
            you want AI to use as an information source. You can select multiple
            documents, one by one.
          </para>
          <figure>
            <title>Selecting documents and collections</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject role="fo">
                <imagedata fileref="openwebui-chat-collections.png" width="75%"/>
              </imageobject>
              <imageobject role="html">
                <imagedata fileref="openwebui-chat-collections.png" width="75%"/>
              </imageobject>
              <textobject role="description"><phrase>Selecting documents and collections</phrase>
              </textobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>
            Instead of selecting the preconfigured documents, you can start
            typing <literal>http:</literal> followed by the full valid URL to
            the page that you want AI to process. After you confirm it with
            <keycap function="enter"/>, AI starts processing it.
          </para>
          <figure>
            <title>Adding a URL source</title>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject role="fo">
                <imagedata fileref="openwebui-chat-url-prompt.png" width="65%"/>
              </imageobject>
              <imageobject role="html">
                <imagedata fileref="openwebui-chat-url-prompt.png" width="65%"/>
              </imageobject>
              <textobject role="description"><phrase>Adding a URL source</phrase>
              </textobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </figure>
        </step>
      </substeps>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Type your prompt and confirm with <keycap function="enter"/> or by clicking
        the <quote>up</quote> arrow to the right of the chat input field.
      </para>
      <figure>
        <title>Prompt with selected documents and collections</title>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject role="fo">
            <imagedata fileref="openwebui-chat-collections-prompt.png" width="75%"/>
          </imageobject>
          <imageobject role="html">
            <imagedata fileref="openwebui-chat-collections-prompt.png" width="75%"/>
          </imageobject>
          <textobject role="description"><phrase>Prompt with selected documents and collections</phrase>
          </textobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        To deactivate the previously selected document from the current chat,
        hover over its name and click the <quote>cross</quote> icon to the right of
        its name.
      </para>
    </step>
  </procedure>
</topic>
